- "have evolved" implies models with more than one version; 
- "are connected" implies models with at least one link; 
- "have been notified about" implies models with at least one notification; 
- "best-performing" refers to models with the highest maximum accuracy; 
- "most recently evaluated" refers to models with the latest evaluation dates.

- The phrase 'latest evaluation metrics' refers to the most recent evaluation performed for each model, based on the 'evaluated_at' date; 
- 'evaluation metrics' include accuracy, precision, recall, F-score, and the time taken for training (training_time); 
- 'configurations' refer to the name, value, and description of the model's configuration parameters; 
- 'integration types' could include version control or CI/CD integrations; 
- The total number of evaluations is calculated for each model across all its versions or updates.
